            "title": "Ajinomoto Recalls a Trader Joe's Chicken-Fried-Rice Item Due to Glass Complaints",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Josh Beckerman </p><br/><p>\n   Ajinomoto Foods North America recalled a Trader Joe's chicken-fried-rice product due to the possible presence of glass, according to the Agriculture Department's Food Safety and Inspection Service. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n   The company notified FSIS of four consumer complaints regarding glass. There have been no confirmed reports of injury, FSIS said. </p><p>\n\n   Ajinomoto Foods, part of Japan-based Ajinomoto Co., recalled about 3.37 million pounds of frozen chicken-fried-rice products overall. This includes an Ajinomoto-brand yakitori-chicken product sold only in Canada. </p><p>\n\n  The products subject to recall bear establishment number P-18356 inside the USDA mark of inspection. The Trader Joe's product has best-by dates of 9/8/2026 through 11/17/2026. The yakitori-chicken item has best-before dates of 26 SE 09 through 26 NO 12. </p><p>\n\n  Ajinomoto Foods North America's other consumer brands include Jose Ole, Ling Ling and Tai Pei. It also has multiple foodservice brands. </p><br/><p>\n  Write to Josh Beckerman at josh.beckerman@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  02-20-26 1350ET</p></div>",
